A man named David Algera (59) is searching for a woman named Annetjie Koch who is allegedy his sister and living in Mbombela.  Algera was spotted two weeks ago sleeping in the bushes at the side of Malie Street, Zandfontein, Pretoria West, by a local, Hennie Olivier. ALSO READ: Intelligence-driven operation leads police to Lows Creek Olivier said Algera had told him that he had a sister named Annetjie Koch living in Nelspruit.  Olivier said Algera was suffering a foot massive infection, but refused to go to hospital and has asked for his family instead.  Friends and family of Olivier have since posted Algera’s details on Facebook in the hopes of finding one of his family members. ALSO READ: A world of gin and good company in White River Olivier has been bringing Algera blankets, jackets and food while the search is ongoing.  Should anyone know anything about Algera’s family’s whereabouts, please contact Olivier on 0826784258.